                     <interp inst="t17730421-2-person102" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a laceman in Buckinghamshire; I come to town very frequently; I have dealt with her seven or eight years; I have left lace at her house from 50 to 200 l. value, and never missed any of it; I have sent lace up to her chamber when she has been ill, and I never missed any of it.</p>
               <p>- Bowlen. I am a laceman; I have dealt with her for hundreds of pounds; I have left cards of lace with her, and always received them as I left them.</p>
